olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
½ Onion
1 packet Asian Greens
½ fresh chilli  (optional)
1 packet ginger paste
3.5 cup boiling water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet oyster sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
1 packet Egg Noodles
1 tsp sesame oil
1 packet Prawn & Chive Wontons
¼ cup water
1 sachet Sesame Seeds

• Boil the kettle.
• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice carrot into half-moons. Thinly slice onion
(see ingredients). Roughly chop Asian greens. Slice fresh chilli (if using).
• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook carrot
and onion, tossing, until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic and ginger paste and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

• To the saucepan, add the boiling water (31/2 cups for 2 people / 7 cups for 4 people), chicken-style stock powder, oyster sauce and the soy sauce.
Stir to combine.
• Add egg noodles then cover with a lid.
• Reduce to a simmer and cook until noodles are tender, 4-5 minutes.

• In the last minute, gently stir noodles with a fork to separate, then add in Asian greens. Stir in the sesame oil and season to taste.
• Meanwhile, in a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook prawn & chive wontons until starting to brown, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water (watch out, it may spatter!), then cover with foil or a lid.
• Cook until the water has evaporated and wontons are tender and heated through, 4-5 minutes.

• Divide veggie noodle soup between bowls.
• Top with prawn & chive wontons.
• Garnish with sesame seeds and fresh chilli to serve. Enjoy!